var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API","text":"","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#Public-surface","page":"API","text":"(More API will appear here as the Phase A implementation lands.)","title":"Public surface"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.AbstractCompartmentLike","page":"API","text":"A piece of mutable state owned by a Component, with a global registry key.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.AbstractCompartmentLike"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent","page":"API","text":"A user-defined biophysical unit; contains Compartments + @compilable methods.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.AbstractContext","page":"API","text":"A named scope holding Components + Processes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.AbstractContext"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.AbstractOp","page":"API","text":"Pure-computation node (no own state, sources from other AbstractValueNodes).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.AbstractOp"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.AbstractProcess","page":"API","text":"A scheduled callable produced from a Component's @compilable method.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.AbstractProcess"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.AbstractValueNode","page":"API","text":"Anything that can appear as a node in a compartment-arithmetic expression.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.AbstractValueNode"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.Compartment","page":"API","text":"Compartment{T}\n\nA typed pointer into the global state dict. After setup!, the canonical key is \"<owner_path>:<name>\" and reads/writes go through GlobalState.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.Compartment"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.Compartment-Tuple{T} where T","page":"API","text":"Compartment(initial_value::T; display_name=nothing, units=nothing,\n            plot_method=nothing, auto_save=true)\n\nConstruct an un-setup Compartment. initial_value is buffered; not written to global state until setup! is called. Mirrors upstream __init__ (compartment.py:39-54).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.Compartment"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.CompiledMethod","page":"API","text":"CompiledMethod\n\nBundle holding the parsed/rewritten artefacts for one @compilable method:\n\nfn::Function       — the compiled pure function (callable directly)\nfn_expr::Expr      — the rewritten function definition Expr\nauxiliary::Vector{Expr} — inlined sub-method definitions (Phase B; empty in A)\nneeded_keys::Set{String} — every compartment key the body reads/writes\ntransformed_kwargs::Set{Symbol} — every kwargs key the body referenced\nsignature_kwargs::Vector{Symbol} — names of every kwarg in the rewritten                                       signature (originally-positional args                                       promoted to required kwargs, plus                                       originally-kwarg args). Used by the                                       Process runner to build keyword_order                                       and route loop_args values via                                       cm.fn(ctx; …kwargs).\n\nCompiledMethod is callable: cm(ctx, args...; kwargs...) invokes cm.fn.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.CompiledMethod"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.CompiledRunner","page":"API","text":"CompiledRunner\n\nOpaque callable: wraps the result of compile_process! (Julia closure) or compile_with_reactant! (Reactant.Compiler.Thunk). Stored on AbstractProcess.compiled as Union{Nothing, CompiledRunner}. Dispatch through (::CompiledRunner)(args...) forwards to the inner payload.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.CompiledRunner"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.Context","page":"API","text":"Context\n\nHolds a name, an absolute colon-path, typed object buckets, and a connection map. Construct via Context (constructor below), which is idempotent by path — calling Context(\"foo\") twice at the same scope returns the same instance.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.Context"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.Context-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"Context(name::AbstractString) -> Context\n\nGet-or-create the Context at <current_path>:<name>. Two calls in the same scope return the same instance — mirrors upstream Context.__new__ (context.py:44-53) with the global-uniqueness-by-path semantic.\n\nDoes NOT enter the scope. Use the do-block form to enter:\n\nContext(\"world\") do ctx\n    # body\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.Context"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.Context-Tuple{Function, AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"Context(f::Function, name::AbstractString) -> Context\n\nDo-block form. Get-or-create, enter the scope, run f(ctx), then exit (popping the path and triggering recompile!). Mirrors Python with Context(\"name\") as ctx: ....\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.Context"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ContextManager","page":"API","text":"ContextManager\n\nProcess-wide registry of every Context plus the mutable \"current path\" that determines which Context auto-captures newly-constructed components.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ContextManager"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ContextObjectType","page":"API","text":"ContextObjectType\n\nEnum mirroring upstream ContextObjectTypes (context.py:20-28). Two values: COMPONENT and PROCESS. The bucket key in Context.objects is the Symbol corresponding to each.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ContextObjectType"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ContextTransformer","page":"API","text":"ContextTransformer\n\nCarries state during a single method-body rewrite.\n\nFields:\n\ninstance::Any          — the live Component instance (for field-resolution)\nctx_sym::Symbol        — name of the ctx-dict parameter in the rewritten signature\nneeded_keys::Set{String} — every compartment root_target referenced\nsub_method::Bool       — true when transforming an inlined sub-method (Phase B)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ContextTransformer"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.GlobalStateManager","page":"API","text":"GlobalStateManager\n\nHolds the entire runtime state of every compartment plus the registry of compartment objects. One per process — see global_state_manager().\n\nFields (private; access via the public API below):\n\nstate::Dict{String,Any}           — <path>:<local_key> → value\ncompartments::Dict{String,AbstractCompartmentLike} — root → compartment\nlock::ReentrantLock               — NEW vs upstream; Python relies on GIL\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.GlobalStateManager"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.GuideKind","page":"API","text":"GuideKind\n\nEnum of guide identifiers exposed by Guides. Mirrors upstream GuideList(Enum) (help.py:58-64). String values preserved for any user code that pickle-style serialises by name.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.GuideKind"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.JointProcess","page":"API","text":"JointProcess\n\nA concrete AbstractProcess that records ordered sub-processes and runs them in sequence. Priority is biased lower-than-lowest-sub on each then! so it always compiles after its sub-processes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.JointProcess"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.JointProcess-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"JointProcess(; name::AbstractString) -> JointProcess\n\nConstruct an empty JointProcess. Add sub-processes via then!(jp, p) or jp >> p.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.JointProcess"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.KwargsTransformer","page":"API","text":"KwargsTransformer\n\nWalks an Expr, rewrites kwargs[KEY] lookups to bare references, and tracks every key that was rewritten in transformed_kwargs.\n\nFields:\n\ntransformed_kwargs::Set{Symbol} — every key extracted from a kwargs[…] lookup\nkwargs_sym::Symbol              — the parameter name that holds kwargs (default :kwargs)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.KwargsTransformer"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.MethodProcess","page":"API","text":"MethodProcess\n\nA concrete AbstractProcess that records ordered (component, method) steps and compiles them into a single pure function via compile_process!.\n\nConstruct via MethodProcess(name=\"…\"). Chain steps via then! or the >> operator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.MethodProcess"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.MethodProcess-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"MethodProcess(; name::AbstractString) -> MethodProcess\n\nConstruct an empty MethodProcess. Caller adds steps via then! or >>, then triggers compile_process! (or closes the enclosing Context block, which calls recompile! on every registered Process).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.MethodProcess"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.Product","page":"API","text":"Product(comps...) <: AbstractOp\n\nElementwise product of value nodes. Identity = 1. Left-fold.\n\nMirrors upstream Product (Product.py:5-19). Note that upstream Summation uses sum(self._comps) (relying on metaclass __add__) while Product does manual comp.get() — asymmetric upstream but consistent here.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.Product"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.Summation","page":"API","text":"Summation(comps...) <: AbstractOp\n\nSums an arbitrary number of value nodes. Identity = 0. Left-fold.\n\nMirrors upstream Summation (Summation.py:5-16).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.Summation"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib._help_section-Tuple{Any, AbstractString, AbstractString, AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"_help_section(data, section_path, section_title, blank_msg; indent=1) -> String\n\nRender a titled \"section\" of a help dict. Walks data along section_path (slash-delimited). If the section is empty/missing:\n\nReturns \"\" when blank_msg == \"\" (matches upstream short-circuit)\nReturns \"<title>:\\n<indent><blank_msg>\\n\" otherwise.\n\nMirrors upstream _HelpSection.write (help.py:4-29).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib._help_section"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib._parse!-Tuple{JointProcess}","page":"API","text":"_parse!(jp::JointProcess) -> Vector{Tuple{AbstractComponent, Symbol}}\n\nFlatten the joint's sub-processes into a single step list. Each sub-process contributes its own _parse! result; the union of all kwargs propagates to jp.keyword_order (handled by compile_process! in BaseProcess.jl).\n\nThe watchlist of each sub-process is merged into `jp.watchlist` (mirrors upstream's mutation at jointProcess.py:53-57).\n\nMirrors upstream JointProcess._parse (jointProcess.py:26-60).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib._parse!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib._parse!-Tuple{MethodProcess}","page":"API","text":"_parse!(p::MethodProcess) -> Vector{Tuple{AbstractComponent, Symbol}}\n\nReturn the step list. Side effect: every component's @compilable methods get lazy-compiled inside compile_process! (via get_compiled). Mirrors upstream MethodProcess._parse (methodProcess.py:52-75).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib._parse!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib._register_compilable!-Tuple{Type, Symbol, AbstractVector, Expr}","page":"API","text":"_register_compilable!(receiver_type::Type, name::Symbol,\n                      args::AbstractVector, body::Expr)\n\nInternal: stash a method's args + body Expr under (receiver_type, name). Called by macro expansion of @compilable.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib._register_compilable!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib._resolve_field_chain-Tuple{Any, Expr}","page":"API","text":"_resolve_field_chain(instance, head::Expr) -> Union{Compartment, Nothing}\n\nGiven a receiver instance and an Expr of the form recv.a.b.c…, walk the chain on the instance and return the resolved Compartment, or nothing if any step fails or the leaf isn't a Compartment.\n\nUsed by the transformer to decide whether a getproperty chain should be rewritten to a ctx[key] read.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib._resolve_field_chain"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.add_compartment!-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractCompartmentLike}","page":"API","text":"add_compartment!(c::AbstractCompartmentLike) -> Nothing\n\nRegister c under its root key. Mirrors upstream add_compartment (manager.py:12-13). c.root must already be set; this is a registration operation, not an allocation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.add_compartment!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.add_connection!-Tuple{Context, NGCSimLib.AbstractValueNode, Compartment}","page":"API","text":"add_connection!(ctx::Context, source::AbstractValueNode, dest::Compartment)\n\nRecord a wire source >> dest for later serialization / introspection. Mirrors upstream add_connection (context.py:227-228).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.add_connection!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.add_key!-Tuple{AbstractString, AbstractString, Any}","page":"API","text":"add_key!(path::AbstractString, local_key::AbstractString, value) -> Nothing\n\nBind value under <path>:<local_key>. Overwrites any existing entry. Mirrors upstream add_key (manager.py:41-52).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.add_key!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.add_logging_level-Tuple{Union{AbstractString, Symbol}, Integer}","page":"API","text":"add_logging_level(name::Union{Symbol,AbstractString}, num::Integer)\n\nRegister a custom log level. Subsequent calls to custom_log(msg, name) or custom_log(msg, num) dispatch to a LogLevel(num) emission. Mirrors upstream addLoggingLevel (logger.py:22-69) but does NOT monkey-patch the stdlib Logging module — Julia's LogLevel is a value type, no global state to mutate.\n\nThrows if name collides with an already-registered Symbol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.add_logging_level"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.append_path-Tuple{ContextManager}","page":"API","text":"append_path(cm::ContextManager; root=nothing, addition=nothing) -> String\n\nCompute <root>:<addition> with edge-case handling. Mirrors upstream append_path (context_manager.py:150-174).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.append_path"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ast_kernel-Tuple{AbstractOp}","page":"API","text":"ast_kernel(op::AbstractOp) -> Function\n\nThe binary reducer associated with this op (e.g. + for Summation, * for Product). Replaces upstream astOp (a Python ast.operator instance) with a direct callable, since Reactant traces Julia functions rather than building AST. Used by lower for the compile path.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ast_kernel"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.check_attributes-Tuple{Any, Union{Nothing, AbstractVector}}","page":"API","text":"check_attributes(obj, required; fatal=false) -> Bool\n\nFor each name (Symbol or String) in required, verify hasproperty(obj, name). If fatal=true and a required name is missing, raises with a useful message; otherwise returns false. required === nothing returns true immediately.\n\nMirrors upstream check_attributes (modules.py:10-40).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.check_attributes"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.check_key-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"check_key(global_key::AbstractString) -> Bool\n\nTrue if global_key is currently present in the state dict. Mirrors upstream check_key (manager.py:30-39).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.check_key"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.check_serializable-Tuple{AbstractDict}","page":"API","text":"check_serializable(d::AbstractDict) -> Vector{String}\n\nReturns the keys of d whose values cannot be JSON-encoded via JSON3.write. Mirrors upstream check_serializable (io.py:37-53), which catches the TypeError from json.dumps. No internal callers — exists for user code that wants to pre-validate save payloads.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.check_serializable"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.clear_compiled!-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"clear_compiled!()\n\nClear the per-instance compiled-method cache. Test/dev helper; useful between independent test sets so cached entries from earlier instances don't shadow.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.clear_compiled!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.clear_contexts!-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"clear_contexts!()\n\nWipe every registered Context and reset the current path. Test/dev helper mirroring upstream clear (context_manager.py:40-45).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.clear_contexts!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.compartments-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent}","page":"API","text":"compartments(c::AbstractComponent) -> Vector{Tuple{Symbol, AbstractCompartmentLike}}\n\nWalk fieldnames(typeof(c)) and return (field_name, compartment) pairs for every field whose value is <: AbstractCompartmentLike. Mirrors upstream Component.compartments property (component.py:19-26) which iterates vars(self) — Julia's fieldnames walk is safer (declared fields only).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.compartments"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.compilable_methods-Tuple{Type}","page":"API","text":"compilable_methods(T::Type) -> Vector{Symbol}\n\nAll method names registered for T (including those registered for any of its supertypes).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.compilable_methods"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.compile_object!-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent}","page":"API","text":"compile_object!(c::AbstractComponent) -> Dict{Symbol,CompiledMethod}\n\nWalk every @compilable method registered for typeof(c) and parse each into a CompiledMethod. Stores the bundle in a per-instance cache and returns it.\n\nMirrors upstream compileObject (utils.py:136-157). Phase A skips sub-Component recursion (no ContextAwareObjectMeta branch yet).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.compile_object!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.compile_process!-Tuple{AbstractProcess}","page":"API","text":"compile_process!(p::AbstractProcess) -> p\n\nWalk the process's step list (via _parse!), compile every component's @compilable methods, gather the union of their needed kwargs into p.keyword_order, and synthesize the spliced runner function as p.compiled.\n\nPhase A: the runner is a plain Julia closure that calls each step sequentially. Phase B will replace with a Reactant-traced one.\n\nMirrors upstream BaseProcess.compile (baseProcess.py:150-209), but emits a closure rather than an AST + exec.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.compile_process!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.compile_with_reactant!-Tuple{AbstractProcess, AbstractDict, AbstractVector}","page":"API","text":"compile_with_reactant!(p::AbstractProcess,\n                       sample_ctx::AbstractDict,\n                       sample_loop_args::AbstractVector) -> p\n\nReplace p.compiled (a Julia-eager closure) with a Reactant.@compile'd traced version. The sample inputs determine the shapes / types Reactant traces against — every subsequent run() call must use compatible shapes (per Reactant's tracing model).\n\nIf compile_process! hasn't been called yet, this triggers it first.\n\nValidated by decisions.md #9 — Reactant 0.2.262 traces through Dict{String,Any} ctx with string-keyed access as constants. No Parser rewrite required.\n\nThrows on first-call shape mismatch. To recompile against different shapes, call compile_process!(p) (reverts to eager) then re-run this.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.compile_with_reactant!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.context_exists-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"context_exists(path::AbstractString) -> Bool\n\nTrue if a Context is registered at path, OR if path is empty (the root always \"exists\" per upstream context_manager.py:105-118).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.context_exists"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.context_path-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent}","page":"API","text":"context_path(c::AbstractComponent) -> String\n\nRead the component's context path — the dot-delimited prefix it was constructed under. Set from ContextManager.current_path at instantiation (Phase A: defaults to \"\" until Context.jl is wired).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.context_path"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.current_context-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"current_context() -> Union{AbstractContext, Nothing}\n\nThe Context registered at the current path, or nothing if none. Mirrors upstream current_context property (context_manager.py:15-21).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.current_context"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.current_location-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"current_location() -> String\n\nLast segment of the current path, or \"\" at root. Mirrors upstream current_location (context_manager.py:23-30).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.current_location"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.current_path-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"current_path() -> String\n\nJoined-string view of the current path stack. Empty string at root.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.current_path"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.custom_log","page":"API","text":"custom_log(msg::AbstractString, level::Union{Symbol,AbstractString,Integer,Nothing}=nothing)\n\nEmit msg at the previously-registered custom level. If level === nothing or unregistered, emits a warning and skips (matches upstream custom_log lines 176-204).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.custom_log"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.deprecate_args-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"deprecate_args(fn; rebind=true, renames::AbstractDict)\n\nWraps fn so that any kwarg key listed in renames triggers an ngc_warn and (if rebind=true) is either renamed to its replacement (when the value is a Symbol/String) or silently dropped (when the value is nothing).\n\nrenames maps old → new (nothing means \"removed entirely\").\n\nMirrors upstream deprecate_args(_rebind=True, **arg_list) (deprecators.py lines 14-35). Differences from upstream:\n\nJulia kwargs are keyword arguments, not a positional dict, so the **arg_list style is replaced with an explicit renames::AbstractDict parameter.\n_rebind is spelled rebind (no leading underscore — that's a Python convention for \"callable-level private\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.deprecate_args"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.from_global_key-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"from_global_key(key::AbstractString) -> Union{Any, Nothing}\n\nSoft lookup by composite key. Returns nothing if absent. Mirrors upstream from_global_key (manager.py:54-63) which uses dict.get(key, None).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.from_global_key"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.from_local_key-Tuple{AbstractString, AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"from_local_key(path::AbstractString, local_key::AbstractString) -> Union{Any, Nothing}\n\nSoft lookup, combining make_key + from_global_key. Mirrors upstream from_local_key (manager.py:65-77).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.from_local_key"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_compartment-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"get_compartment(root::AbstractString) -> AbstractCompartmentLike\n\nLook up a registered compartment by its root key. Throws KeyError if missing, matching upstream get_compartment (manager.py:15-16) which does a bare dict[key] lookup with no fallback.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_compartment"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_compilable_body-Tuple{Type, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"get_compilable_body(T::Type, name::Symbol) -> Expr\n\nRetrieve the registered body Expr for (T, name), walking supertypes if necessary. Raises if not registered.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_compilable_body"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_compilable_entry-Tuple{Type, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"get_compilable_entry(T::Type, name::Symbol) -> NamedTuple{(:args, :body), …}\n\nInternal: full registry entry for (T, name), walking supertypes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_compilable_entry"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_compilable_signature-Tuple{Type, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"get_compilable_signature(T::Type, name::Symbol) -> Vector{Any}\n\nRetrieve the registered arg list Vector for (T, name). First element is the receiver (e.g. :(c::T)), rest are the method's positional/kwarg specs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_compilable_signature"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_compiled-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"get_compiled(c::AbstractComponent, method_name::Symbol) -> CompiledMethod\n\nLook up the parsed CompiledMethod for (c, method_name). Calls compile_object!(c) lazily if no bundle exists yet.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_compiled"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_components-Tuple{Context}","page":"API","text":"get_components(ctx::Context) -> Dict{String,Any}\n\nAlias for get_objects_by_type(ctx, COMPONENT). Matches upstream get_components (context.py:220-225).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_components"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_config-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"get_config(name::AbstractString) -> Union{Any, Nothing}\n\nReturns loadedConfig[name] or nothing if (a) init_config was never called, or (b) the key is absent. Mirrors upstream get_config (configManager.py:18-25). Two guards, both return None silently.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_config"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_context-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"get_context(path::AbstractString) -> Union{AbstractContext, Nothing}\n\nLookup by joined-string path. Mirrors upstream get_context (context_manager.py:93-103).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_context"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_needed_keys-Tuple{AbstractOp}","page":"API","text":"get_needed_keys(op::AbstractOp) -> Set{String}\n\nUnion of get_needed_keys across all operands. Mirrors upstream get_needed_keys (BaseOp.py:66-73) — fixing the upstream bug where the non-mutating keys.union(...) return is discarded (spec §\"Hazards\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_needed_keys"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_needed_keys-Tuple{Compartment}","page":"API","text":"get_needed_keys(c::Compartment) -> Set{String}\n\nThe set of global-state keys this compartment needs to read. Mirrors upstream get_needed_keys (compartment.py:101-108), but without the upstream bug (spec Open Question #2). Upstream's set(self.target) on a string produces individual characters; we return Set([target]) with the whole key.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_needed_keys"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_objects_by_type-Tuple{Context, ContextObjectType}","page":"API","text":"get_objects_by_type(ctx::Context, ot::ContextObjectType) -> Dict{String,Any}\n\nBucket lookup. Returns an empty Dict if the bucket is absent. Mirrors upstream get_objects_by_type (context.py:157-173).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_objects_by_type"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_priority-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"get_priority(fn) -> Int\n\nLook up the priority registered for fn. Returns 0 if unregistered, matching upstream getattr(obj, \"_priority\", None) or 0 fallback (context.py:85,93,334).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_priority"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_processes-Tuple{Context}","page":"API","text":"get_processes(ctx::Context) -> Dict{String,Any}\n\nPhase-A add-on, not in upstream — symmetry with get_components.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_processes"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_state-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"get_state() -> Dict{String,Any}\n\nReturns a defensive copy of the state dict. Mutating the result does NOT mutate the singleton. Mirrors upstream state property (manager.py:88-93) which returns self.__state.copy().\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_state"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_value-Tuple{AbstractOp}","page":"API","text":"get_value(op::AbstractOp) -> Any\n\nRequired interface. Concrete ops MUST implement this. Default raises rather than silently returning a sentinel (departure from upstream BaseOp._get_value -> NotImplemented, per spec recommendation).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_value"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.get_value-Tuple{Compartment}","page":"API","text":"get_value(c::Compartment) -> Any\n\nResolve c's current value. Mirrors upstream _get_value (compartment.py:110-117):\n\npre-setup → initial_value\ntarget is an Op → recurse via get_value(target)\ntarget is a String → read from global state; initial_value fallback if absent\n\nThe get_value(::AbstractValueNode) generic is the canonical Compartment ↔ Op interface — both implement it; arithmetic unwraps through it.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.get_value"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.guides-Tuple{AbstractDict}","page":"API","text":"guides(data::AbstractDict) -> NamedTuple\n\nRender all five guides at once, returning a NamedTuple for dot-access. Mirrors upstream Guides(base_cls) constructor (help.py:67-110), which populates self.inputs, self.outputs, self.monitoring, self.params, self.wiring.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.guides"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.has_priority-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"has_priority(fn) -> Bool\n\nTrue iff fn has been explicitly tagged via priority!. Distinguishes the \"unregistered, defaulted to 0\" case from \"explicitly tagged with 0\".\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.has_priority"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.init_config-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"init_config(path::AbstractString) -> Nothing\n\nRead a JSON file from path and stash it as the global config dict. Mirrors upstream init_config (configManager.py:14-16). Throws on missing file or JSON parse error — upstream does too (no try/except wrap).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.init_config"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.init_logging-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"init_logging(; logging_file=nothing, logging_level=Error, hide_console=false,\n              custom_levels::AbstractDict=Dict{Symbol,Int}())\n\nIdempotent logger setup. Mirrors upstream init_logging (logger.py:72-105). Installs any custom_levels first (so they're available to subsequent file/ console output), then constructs a logger that:\n\nwrites to stderr (unless hide_console=true)\ntees to logging_file (mode \"a+\") if given, prepended with the upstream ~~~~~/New Log <UTC timestamp>/~~~~~ banner\n\nlogging_level may be a Logging.LogLevel, an Int, or a Symbol/String (uppercased and matched against the stdlib names: Debug / Info / Warn / Error — and any name previously installed via add_logging_level).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.init_logging"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.is_compilable_method-Tuple{Type, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"is_compilable_method(T::Type, name::Symbol) -> Bool\n\nTrue iff a method named name was defined with @compilable for receivers of type T (or any supertype of T that registered the method).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.is_compilable_method"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.is_compiled-Tuple{AbstractProcess}","page":"API","text":"is_compiled(p::AbstractProcess) -> Bool\n\nTrue if compile_process! has populated p.compiled. Mirrors upstream is_compiled (baseProcess.py:108-109).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.is_compiled"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.is_deprecated-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"is_deprecated(fn) -> Bool\n\nTrue iff fn is a wrapper produced by @deprecated or deprecate_args. Mirrors upstream getattr(fn, \"_is_deprecated\", False).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.is_deprecated"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.join_path","page":"API","text":"join_path(cm::ContextManager, path=nothing) -> String\n\nJoin path (or the current path if nothing) into a colon-string. Mirrors upstream join_path (context_manager.py:120-133).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.join_path"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.keyword_order-Tuple{AbstractProcess}","page":"API","text":"keyword_order(p::AbstractProcess) -> Vector{Symbol}\n\nOrdered list of kwarg names this process expects at run time. Populated during compile_process! from the union of each step's parser-detected kwargs. Mirrors upstream _keyword_order (baseProcess.py:65).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.keyword_order"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.load_attribute-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"load_attribute(attribute_name; module_path=nothing, match_case=false, absolute_path=false) -> Any\n\nResolve a named attribute (typically a type or function) from a module.\n\nIf module_path === nothing, uses attribute_name as the module name too. If match_case=false, capitalises only the first letter of attribute_name before getfield — so load_attribute(\"rateCell\") looks up RateCell. Does NOT lowercase the rest (spec Open Question #3 — port verbatim).\n\nCaches in _LOADED_ATTRIBUTES. Raises on miss. Mirrors upstream load_attribute (modules.py:120-165).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.load_attribute"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.load_from_path-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"load_from_path(path; match_case=false, absolute_path=false) -> Any\n\nConvenience: when absolute_path=true, splits path on the last dot into module_name (prefix) + attribute_name (suffix), then forces match_case=true (preserves the exact spelling of the requested attribute). Otherwise, treats the whole path as both module name and attribute name.\n\nMirrors upstream load_from_path (modules.py:90-117).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.load_from_path"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.load_module-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"load_module(module_path; match_case=false, absolute_path=false) -> Module\n\nResolve a module by name. With absolute_path=true, treats module_path as a registered package name and Base.require's it. Otherwise scans Base.loaded_modules for any module whose nameof matches the last dot-component of module_path (case-insensitive by default).\n\nCaches resolutions in _LOADED_MODULES. Raises an ErrorException (upstream RuntimeError) on lookup failure. Mirrors upstream load_module (modules.py:43-87).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.load_module"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.lower-Tuple{AbstractOp, Any}","page":"API","text":"lower(op::AbstractOp, ctx)\n\nRecursive lowering for the compile path. Each operand is lowered (Compartments become ctx[target], nested ops recurse), then the op's ast_kernel is left-folded across them. Mirrors upstream BaseOp._to_ast (BaseOp.py:30-51).\n\nSingle-operand ops pass through (spec line 188).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.lower"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.make_key-Tuple{AbstractString, AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"make_key(path::AbstractString, local_key::AbstractString) -> String\n\nBuild the composite global key. Mirrors upstream make_key (manager.py:18-28): f\"{path}:{local_key}\". Pure function — no state access, no lock needed.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.make_key"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.make_safe_filename-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"make_safe_filename(name; replacement=\"_\") -> String\n\nSanitize name for use as a filename. Replaces spaces and any of <>:\"/\\|?* plus ASCII control chars \\x00-\\x1F with replacement, then trims trailing whitespace.\n\nMirrors upstream regex r'[ <>:\"/\\\\|?*\\0-\\31]' (io.py:3-5).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.make_safe_filename"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.make_unique_path","page":"API","text":"make_unique_path(directory, root_name=nothing) -> String\n\nGenerate (and mkdir) a unique subdirectory under directory. If root_name === nothing, names it with a fresh UUIDv4. If root_name is given but directory/root_name already exists, appends _<uuid4>.\n\nReturns the new path. Mirrors upstream make_unique_path (io.py:7-34).\n\nSide effect: println (NOT logger) reports the chosen name. This matches upstream behaviour — see Open Question #10 in the support spec.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.make_unique_path"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.name-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent}","page":"API","text":"name(c::AbstractComponent) -> String\n\nRead the component's identifier. Subtypes must declare a name::String field. Mirrors upstream self.name set by ContextAwareObject.__init__ (contextAwareObject.py:16-18).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.name"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ngc_critical-Tuple","page":"API","text":"ngc_critical(args...; sep=\" \", finish=\"\")\n\nLog at Critical level (custom LogLevel 2000, above Error) THEN throw an ErrorException. Control flow. Mirrors upstream critical() (logger.py:136-147) which always raises RuntimeError regardless of caller intent — the errortype knob is intentionally NOT exposed here (matching upstream behavior).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ngc_critical"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ngc_debug-Tuple","page":"API","text":"ngc_debug(args...; sep=\" \", finish=\"\")\n\nLog a debug message. Does NOT raise. Equivalent to upstream debug() (logger.py:163-173).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ngc_debug"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ngc_error-Tuple","page":"API","text":"ngc_error(args...; errortype::Type{<:Exception}=ErrorException, sep=\" \", finish=\"\")\n\nLog at Error level THEN throw(errortype(msg)). This is control flow — callers expect it to abort the current execution path. Mirrors upstream error() exactly (logger.py:121-133), preserving the raise-on-error semantic that the rest of ngcsimlib depends on.\n\nDifferent from Base.error only in that it also emits a log record before the throw.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ngc_error"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ngc_info-Tuple","page":"API","text":"ngc_info(args...; sep=\" \", finish=\"\")\n\nLog an info message. Does NOT raise. Equivalent to upstream info() (logger.py:150-160).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ngc_info"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.ngc_warn-Tuple","page":"API","text":"ngc_warn(args...; sep=\" \", finish=\"\")\n\nLog a warning. Does NOT raise. Args are joined with sep (default \" \") mirroring Python print. Equivalent to upstream warn() (logger.py:108-118).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.ngc_warn"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.operands-Tuple{AbstractOp}","page":"API","text":"operands(op::AbstractOp) -> Vector{AbstractValueNode}\n\nRead-access to the operand list. All concrete ops store a comps field; the default accessor returns it. Override if a future op uses a different field name.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.operands"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.original_of-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"original_of(fn) -> Any\n\nReturns the unwrapped original if fn is a deprecation wrapper, else fn itself. Mirrors upstream fn._original.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.original_of"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.pack_keywords-Tuple{AbstractProcess}","page":"API","text":"pack_keywords(p::AbstractProcess; row_seed=nothing, kwargs...) -> Vector\n\nFor each key in p.keyword_order, pick kwargs[key]. If the value is a callable, call it with row_seed (which must be given). Returns a Vector in keyword_order order. Mirrors upstream pack_keywords (baseProcess.py:56-86).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.pack_keywords"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.pack_rows-Tuple{AbstractProcess, Integer}","page":"API","text":"pack_rows(p::AbstractProcess, length::Integer;\n          seed_generator=identity, kwargs...) -> Vector{Vector}\n\nProduce length rows, each generated via pack_keywords(p; row_seed=seed_generator(i), kwargs...). Mirrors upstream pack_rows (baseProcess.py:88-106).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.pack_rows"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.parse_method-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"parse_method(instance::AbstractComponent, method_name::Symbol;\n             ctx_sym::Symbol=:ctx, kwargs_sym::Symbol=:kwargs) -> CompiledMethod\n\nTake the body Expr registered by @compilable for (typeof(instance), method_name), rewrite it via ContextTransformer (compartment access → ctx-dict access) and KwargsTransformer (kwargs subscripts → bare locals), then wrap into a freshly evaluated function. Returns the CompiledMethod bundle.\n\nMirrors upstream parse_method (utils.py:88-113) but skips the recursion into sub-methods / sub-Components for Phase A scope.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.parse_method"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.post_init!-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent}","page":"API","text":"post_init!(c::AbstractComponent) -> AbstractComponent\n\nThe \"after the constructor returns\" hook that:\n\nCaptures context_path from the active ContextManager (no-op if c already has a non-empty context_path).\nFor each Compartment field of c, calls setup! with field_name and <context_path>:<c.name> — establishing the full global-state key \"<ctx>:<comp>:<field>\".\nIf a current_context() is active, calls register_obj! to record c in the enclosing Context's COMPONENT bucket.\n\nMirrors upstream ContextAwareObjectMeta.__call__ (Meta.py:48-70) without the metaclass machinery. Returns c for chaining.\n\nIdempotent — calling twice is safe but inefficient (re-runs setup!).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.post_init!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.priority!-Tuple{Any, Integer}","page":"API","text":"priority!(fn, value::Integer) -> fn\n\nTag fn with priority value. Returns fn unmodified — the registry is the only thing that changed. Mirrors upstream @priority(value) decorator (priority.py lines 1-7); registers in place and returns the callable.\n\n! suffix per Julia convention: mutates external state (the registry).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.priority!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.provide_namespace-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"provide_namespace(name::AbstractString) -> Union{NamedTuple, Nothing}\n\nReturns the section as a NamedTuple for dot-access (cfg.logging_level), or nothing if the section is absent. Mirrors upstream provide_namespace which wraps the dict in types.SimpleNamespace (configManager.py:27-32).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.provide_namespace"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.recompile!-Tuple{Context}","page":"API","text":"recompile!(ctx::Context) -> Nothing\n\nIterate every object in every bucket, collect is_compilable_method-marked ones, sort by priority descending, and call compile! on each. Phase A stub: walks objects but skips the actual compile! step — the Parser hasn't landed yet.\n\nMirrors upstream Context.recompile (context.py:75-103).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.recompile!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.register_context!-Tuple{AbstractString, NGCSimLib.AbstractContext}","page":"API","text":"register_context!(path::AbstractString, ctx::AbstractContext;\n                   overwrite::Bool=false) -> Bool\n\nInsert ctx into the global registry under path. With overwrite=false (default), refuses to clobber an existing entry and emits a warn. Mirrors upstream register_context (context_manager.py:176-197).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.register_context!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.register_context_local!-Tuple{AbstractString, NGCSimLib.AbstractContext}","page":"API","text":"register_context_local!(local_path::AbstractString, ctx::AbstractContext;\n                         overwrite::Bool=true) -> Bool\n\nRegister ctx at <current_path>:<local_path>. Note overwrite=true by default (different from register_context!) — mirrors upstream's asymmetric default at context_manager.py:199-213.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.register_context_local!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.register_obj!-Tuple{Context, Any}","page":"API","text":"register_obj!(ctx::Context, obj) -> Bool\n\nAdd obj to the appropriate type bucket. Mirrors upstream Context.registerObj (context.py:105-155) but keyed by name(obj) for both store and duplicate-check — upstream has a bug keying duplicate detection by object identity (spec hazard). Returns false if obj lacks a known object_type.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.register_obj!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.remove_context!-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"remove_context!(path::AbstractString) -> Bool\n\nDelete the registration at path. Returns true if anything was removed. Mirrors upstream remove_context (context_manager.py:215-232).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.remove_context!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.render_guide-Tuple{AbstractDict, GuideKind}","page":"API","text":"render_guide(data::AbstractDict, kind::GuideKind) -> String\n\nRender one of the five canonical guides from a data dict produced by a component's help() method. Mirrors upstream Guides.__write_guide (help.py:111-123, called for each kind).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.render_guide"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.reset_config!-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"reset_config!() -> Nothing\n\nTest helper: clears the singleton. Not in upstream surface but needed because Julia tests share module state across testsets.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.reset_config!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.reset_global_state!-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"reset_global_state!() -> Nothing\n\nClear the singleton's state + compartment dicts. Not in upstream surface; needed for test isolation. Does NOT replace the lock — same lock survives.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.reset_global_state!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.reset_module_caches!-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"reset_module_caches!()\n\nClear _LOADED_MODULES and _LOADED_ATTRIBUTES. Not in upstream surface; needed for test isolation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.reset_module_caches!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.root-Tuple{Compartment}","page":"API","text":"root(c::Compartment) -> Union{String, Nothing}\n\nThe canonical, immutable global-state key for c. nothing before setup!. Mirrors upstream root property (compartment.py:56-58).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.root"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.run-Tuple{AbstractProcess}","page":"API","text":"run(p::AbstractProcess; state=nothing, keywords=nothing,\n                        update::Bool=true, row_seed=nothing,\n                        kwargs...) -> (ctx, watched)\n\nExecute the compiled process. Mirrors upstream BaseProcess.run (baseProcess.py:111-144).\n\nDefaults:\n\nstate=nothing     → use get_state() snapshot of the global manager\nkeywords=nothing  → call pack_keywords(p; row_seed=row_seed, kwargs...)\nupdate=true       → write the mutated ctx back via set_state!\n\nThrows if not yet compiled.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.run"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.set!-Tuple{Compartment, Any}","page":"API","text":"set!(c::Compartment, value)\n\nWrite value into c's slot. Behavior depends on target:\n\npre-setup (target === nothing)     → buffer in initial_value\nwired to non-root (foreign target)   → log warn, abort\nown slot (target == root_target)   → write through to global state\n\nMirrors upstream set (compartment.py:76-93).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.set!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.set_state!-Tuple{AbstractDict}","page":"API","text":"set_state!(state::AbstractDict) -> Nothing\n\nPartial-overwrite semantics (merge, not replace). Mirrors upstream set_state (manager.py:79-86) which does self.__state.update(state). A JIT-compiled process body produces only the keys it touched; this merges them back into the singleton without dropping untouched keys.\n\nThe setter version gsm.state = {...} in Python (manager.py:95-102) also delegates to update, so there is no \"full replace\" path in the upstream API at all.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.set_state!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.setup!-Tuple{Compartment, AbstractString, AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"setup!(c::Compartment, comp_name::AbstractString, path::AbstractString)\n\nRegister c into the global state. Assigns name and root_target, defaults target to root_target if not pre-wired, writes initial_value into the global state dict, and registers the Compartment with the manager.\n\nMirrors upstream _setup (compartment.py:68-74). This is the moment a Compartment becomes \"live.\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.setup!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.split_path","page":"API","text":"split_path(cm::ContextManager, path=nothing) -> Vector{String}\n\nSplit path (or current) into segments. Mirrors upstream split_path (contextmanager.py:135-148). Returns a copy of `currentpathwhenpath === nothing`, not the live vector (departure from upstream — the upstream aliasing was flagged as a hazard).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.split_path"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.step!-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"step!(location::AbstractString; catch_empty::Bool=true) -> Bool\n\nPush one segment onto the current path. Returns true iff a context exists at the new path. With catch_empty=true (default), warns when stepping into a non-existent context. Mirrors upstream step (context_manager.py:47-63).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.step!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.step_back!-Tuple{}","page":"API","text":"step_back!() -> Bool\n\nPop one segment off the current path. Returns false at root (no-op). Mirrors upstream step_back (context_manager.py:65-73).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.step_back!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.step_to!-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"API","text":"step_to!(path::AbstractString) -> Bool\n\nReplace current_path with split_path(path). Returns true always (matches upstream's step_to behavior at context_manager.py:91 — the docstring claimed to return the existence flag but the code returns True unconditionally; we keep faithful here and warn on missing).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.step_to!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.target!-Tuple{Compartment, Any}","page":"API","text":"target!(c::Compartment, value)\n\nSet c.target. value must be a String, AbstractValueNode (op), or another Compartment (in which case we chase one hop to value.target). Mirrors upstream target setter (compartment.py:150-170), with the unreachable branches collapsed per spec Open Question #3.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.target!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.target-Tuple{Compartment}","page":"API","text":"target(c::Compartment) -> Union{Nothing, String, AbstractValueNode}\n\nThe current read source. Mirrors upstream target property (compartment.py:143-148).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.target"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.targeted-Tuple{Compartment}","page":"API","text":"targeted(c::Compartment) -> Bool\n\nTrue iff c has been wired to read from a non-canonical source. Mirrors upstream targeted property (compartment.py:64-66).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.targeted"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.then!-Tuple{JointProcess, AbstractProcess}","page":"API","text":"then!(jp::JointProcess, sub::AbstractProcess) -> jp\n\nAppend sub to the joint's order. Adjusts jp's priority to sub.priority - 1 if necessary so the joint always compiles after its newest sub. Mirrors upstream JointProcess.then (jointProcess.py:16-22).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.then!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.then!-Tuple{MethodProcess, NGCSimLib.AbstractComponent, Symbol}","page":"API","text":"then!(p::MethodProcess, c::AbstractComponent, method_name::Symbol) -> p\n\nAppend (c, method_name) to the method order. The method must have been defined with @compilable on the receiver type. Mirrors upstream MethodProcess.then (methodProcess.py:38-47).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.then!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.transform_kwargs-Tuple{Expr}","page":"API","text":"transform_kwargs(body::Expr; kwargs_sym=:kwargs) -> (rewritten::Expr, keys::Set{Symbol})\n\nConvenience: build a transformer, walk body, return (rewritten, keys).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.transform_kwargs"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.unwrap-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractValueNode}","page":"API","text":"unwrap(x) -> Any\n\nRecursive value resolution. Loops get_value until the receiver is no longer an AbstractValueNode. Mirrors upstream _unwrap (compartmentMeta.py:5-8).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.unwrap"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.view_compiled-Tuple{AbstractProcess}","page":"API","text":"view_compiled(p::AbstractProcess) -> String\n\nReturn a human-readable view of the compiled runner. Phase A: lists the step sequence + kwargs + watched. Phase B: emit the full spliced Expr.\n\nMirrors upstream view_compiled_method (baseProcess.py:28-35).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.view_compiled"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.visit-Tuple{ContextTransformer, Any}","page":"API","text":"visit(t::ContextTransformer, e) -> Expr | atom\n\nRecursively rewrite e. Atoms (Symbol, literal, QuoteNode) pass through unless an enclosing Expr decides otherwise.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.visit"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.visit-Tuple{KwargsTransformer, Any}","page":"API","text":"visit(t::KwargsTransformer, e) -> Expr | atom\n\nRewrite kwargs[:foo] / kwargs[\"foo\"] → foo, recording :foo in transformed_kwargs. Mirrors upstream visit_Subscript (kwargsTransformer.py:8-15).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.visit"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.watch!-Tuple{AbstractProcess, Vararg{Compartment}}","page":"API","text":"watch!(p::AbstractProcess, compartments::Compartment...) -> p\n\nMark each compartment for inclusion in the watched-tuple returned by run. Mirrors upstream BaseProcess.watch (baseProcess.py:38-46).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.watch!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.watch_list-Tuple{AbstractProcess}","page":"API","text":"watch_list(p::AbstractProcess) -> Vector{Compartment}\n\nCompartments whose final values are returned (as a tuple) alongside the mutated ctx. Mirrors upstream _watch_list (baseProcess.py:62).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.watch_list"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.wire!-Tuple{NGCSimLib.AbstractValueNode, Compartment}","page":"API","text":"wire!(source::AbstractValueNode, dest::Compartment)\n\nRetarget dest to read from source. Used by the >> operator. If there's a current context, the wire is recorded via add_connection!.\n\nMirrors upstream __rrshift__ (compartment.py:134-137). Returns dest.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.wire!"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.@compilable-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"@compilable function name(c::MyComponent, ...) ... end\n\nMark a method as JIT-compilable. Both:\n\nDefines the method normally (eager Julia dispatch still works).\nRegisters the method body Expr in _COMPILABLE_METHODS for the Parser to consume at compile time.\n\nThe first argument's type annotation determines the receiver type used as the registry key. Methods without a typed first arg fall back to Any (useful only for free functions; not the intended use).\n\nMirrors upstream @compilable (parser/utils.py:8-16) which sets fn._is_compilable = True and is checked by the Parser when walking class methods.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.@compilable"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.@context_aware-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"@context_aware ConstructorCall\n\nConvenience macro: wraps a constructor call so post_init! is invoked on the returned instance automatically. Mirrors what upstream's metaclass does invisibly — here it's opt-in and explicit.\n\n@context_aware RateCell(name=\"layer1\", voltage=Compartment(zeros(16)))\n\nis equivalent to:\n\nlet c = RateCell(name=\"layer1\", voltage=Compartment(zeros(16)))\n    post_init!(c)\nend\n\nOptional for @ngc_component types — post_init!(c) can be called directly. Phase B may inject this into the generated kw constructor so the macro becomes mandatory only for hand-rolled subtypes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.@context_aware"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.@deprecated-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"@deprecated fn\n\nWraps fn so that each call emits an ngc_warn and then delegates. The wrapper is registered so is_deprecated(wrapper) == true and original_of(wrapper) === fn. Mirrors upstream deprecated() decorator (deprecators.py lines 4-11).\n\nUsage:     foo = @deprecated oldfoo     foo(1, 2)   # emits \"oldfoo is deprecated\" then calls old_foo(1, 2)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.@deprecated"},{"category":"macro","location":"api/#NGCSimLib.@ngc_component-Tuple{Any}","page":"API","text":"@ngc_component mutable struct Foo\n    v::Compartment{Vector{Float32}}\n    # ... more fields\nend\n\nInject the standard name::String, context_path::String, args::Vector{Any}, kwargs::Dict{Symbol,Any} fields plus <: AbstractComponent supertype declaration, then emit a kw-style constructor that defaults the standard fields and accepts the user-declared fields as keyword arguments.\n\nUsage:\n\n@ngc_component mutable struct RateCell\n    voltage::Compartment{Vector{Float32}}\nend\n\ncell = RateCell(name=\"layer1\",\n                voltage = Compartment(zeros(Float32, 16)))\n\nManual alternative: declare your own mutable struct Foo <: AbstractComponent with the same five standard fields plus your compartments. The macro is a convenience, not a requirement.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"NGCSimLib.@ngc_component"},{"category":"section","location":"getting_started/architecture/#Architecture","page":"Architecture","text":"See NGCSimLib_design.md for the full design document. The per-module ports from upstream Python are in docs/specs/.","title":"Architecture"},{"category":"section","location":"getting_started/architecture/#Abstract-type-hierarchy","page":"Architecture","text":"AbstractValueNode\n├── AbstractCompartmentLike\n│   └── Compartment{T}\n└── AbstractOp\n    ├── Summation\n    └── Product\n\nAbstractComponent       # owns Compartments + @compilable methods\nAbstractContext         # named scope holding Components\nAbstractProcess         # scheduled callable from @compilable methods","title":"Abstract type hierarchy"},{"category":"section","location":"getting_started/architecture/#Compilation-pipeline","page":"Architecture","text":"User code (@compilable function ... end)\n  │ macro captures Expr at definition site\n  ▼\nPer-type @compilable registry\n  │ Component constructed in `with_context(ctx) do ... end`\n  ▼\ncompile_object!(component) — walks Expr through ContextTransformer:\n  self.x         → ctx[Symbol(\"path:to:x\")]\n  self.x = v     → merge ctx with new value\n  sub.method(..) → graft compiled AST\n  ▼\neval → pure function (ctx::NamedTuple, kwargs...) → ctx\n  ▼\nProcess wraps one or more compiled methods\n  ▼\nReactant.@compile → StableHLO/XLA\n  ▼\nrun!(process, kwargs...)\n\nThe Reactant integration is at the END — after AST rewriting + eval. The parser produces pure functions; Reactant traces those; Enzyme differentiates them.","title":"Compilation pipeline"},{"category":"section","location":"getting_started/installation/#Installation","page":"Getting Started","text":"NGCSimLib requires Julia 1.10 or later.","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"getting_started/installation/#From-GitHub-(current-—-pre-registration)","page":"Getting Started","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url = \"https://github.com/CognitiveSubstratesAI/NGCSimLib\")","title":"From GitHub (current — pre-registration)"},{"category":"section","location":"getting_started/installation/#Verify-the-install","page":"Getting Started","text":"using NGCSimLib\n@info \"NGCSimLib version $(NGCSimLib.NGCSIMLIB_VERSION)\"","title":"Verify the install"},{"category":"section","location":"getting_started/installation/#Dev-install","page":"Getting Started","text":"To work on the package itself:\n\ngit clone https://github.com/CognitiveSubstratesAI/NGCSimLib.git\ncd NGCSimLib\njulia --project=. -e 'using Pkg; Pkg.instantiate(); Pkg.test()'","title":"Dev install"},{"category":"section","location":"getting_started/installation/#Compute-backend","page":"Getting Started","text":"NGCSimLib depends on:\n\nReactant.jl for JIT compilation to MLIR/StableHLO (analog of JAX's jit)\nEnzyme.jl for automatic differentiation (analog of JAX's grad)\n\nBoth work on CPU by default. GPU support follows Reactant's backend matrix.","title":"Compute backend"},{"category":"section","location":"#NGCSimLib","page":"Home","text":"Julia port of NACLab's ngc-sim-lib. The substrate layer of the NGC stack — Component / Compartment / Context / Process — for building biophysical and neurobiological simulation graphs in Julia.","title":"NGCSimLib"},{"category":"section","location":"#What-is-NGCSimLib?","page":"Home","text":"NGCSimLib is the simulation substrate that all higher-level NACLab models are built on. It provides:\n\nComponent — a user-defined biophysical unit (neuron, synapse, encoder…)\nCompartment — a piece of mutable state owned by a Component, with arithmetic-overloaded so you can write neuron.v >> synapse.input to wire things together\nContext — a named scope that holds Components and orchestrates their registration into the global state graph\nProcess — a scheduled callable produced by AST-rewriting a Component's @compilable method into a pure function, JIT-compiled via Reactant.jl\n\nPages = [\n    \"getting_started/installation.md\",\n    \"getting_started/architecture.md\",\n    \"api/index.md\",\n]\nDepth = 2","title":"What is NGCSimLib?"},{"category":"section","location":"#NGC-stack-position","page":"Home","text":"NGCSimLib is Layer 0:\n\nLayer Package Purpose\n0 (substrate) NGCSimLib (this) Component / Compartment / Context / Process\n1 (model zoo) NGCLearn.jl 11+ neuron families, 40+ synapse families, encoders, integrators\n2 (PC framework) FabricPC.jl Predictive coding graph: nodes, wires, energy minimization, muPC scaling\n\nEach layer is its own GitHub repo, each can be installed independently.","title":"NGC stack position"},{"category":"section","location":"#Status","page":"Home","text":"Phase A scaffold — the package loads, type hierarchy is in place, every source file exists as a documented stub. Implementation lands incrementally with acceptance gates per ngc-museum exhibit reproduction.","title":"Status"},{"category":"section","location":"#Citation","page":"Home","text":"If you use this work, please also cite the upstream ngc-sim-lib:\n\n@article{ororbia2022neural,\n  title   = {The neural coding framework for learning generative models},\n  author  = {Ororbia, Alexander and Kifer, Daniel},\n  journal = {Nature Communications},\n  volume  = {13},\n  number  = {1},\n  pages   = {2064},\n  year    = {2022}\n}","title":"Citation"}]
}
